The annual total solar radiation, It on an optimally inclined solar collector, hours of sunshine, hs and average ambient temperature, Ta, are presented in Fig. 11. The comfort temperature, Tc used for analysing the heat load of the building, was set as 18 °C. As can be seen year round solar irradiation is in the range of 4 → 7.5 kWh, ambient temperature is 12 → 28 °C and daily sunshine is in the range of 9.5 → 14 h. According to these data, it is clear that Cyprus has a remarkable year round solar availability to utilize in thermal applications. Data obtained from the European Commission’s web site (http://re.jrc.ec.europa.eu/pvgis/apps4/pvest.php?lang=en&map=europe. [Accessed on 10.01.2015], http://photovoltaic-software.com/pvgis.php) was used to calculate the solar thermal heat gain, Qu (W) using Eq. 1:Fig. 11
